<br>
The grand illusion is to have content to match the players capacity. Old content serves to reaffirm the illusion. We are the suckers that buy (and pay for) that illusion. <br>
<br>
New level cap or not, they need to make current hard dungeons more trivial, so that we feel like we are improving. Whether they do it with levels or AA points is utterly unimportant. <br>
<br>
In a year, HoT will be single groupable, and people will smile at people who needs 2 or 3 groups to go there. Just like Sebilis/chardok/etc. <br>
<br>
It is the basic drive of most computer games that players become more powerfull all the time. Old content becomes trivial. People move to new places to fight...<br>
<br>
And I don't believe people who says that they will quit game if that happens. If they made it to this stage, they are as addicted as any of us =).<br>
