<br>
1) meaningful advancement(wether by cost-scaling aaxp abilities or levels) is available in which case old content becomes trival, content disapears for some lowbies and the issues surounding trivialization of code continues.<br>
<br>
2) no meaningful advancement is available in which case a HUGE number of high level players who are at or are rapidly approaching the end of useful aaxp will have no real way to progress in the game without joining a &quot;uber guild&quot; and the time drain associated...<br>
<br>
This really is a no win situation, regardless of what VI chooses to do they will lose customers over it as is life.<br>
<br>
But personally I would rather have meaningful advancement in ways that don't require 50+ people gang banging a mob and hoping that lag/ld's doesn't screw up 3 or 4 hours of work. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukaenneth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaenneth</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#333333>(9/12/02 9:20:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=339.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what people seem to forget...</span><hr size=1> I want Racial and Diety AAXP catagories.<br>
